# Agent Instructions

## Skill Capabilities

When you load a skill that has `requires` in its metadata, resolve each capability against this list. If a capability isn't listed, find a skill in `~/.agents/skills/` whose `provides` list includes it — otherwise ask the user which provider to use.

{{ $caps := fromYaml (include "skills/capabilities.yaml") -}}
{{ range $cap, $entry := $caps -}}
{{ $provider := "" -}}
{{ $notes := "" -}}
{{ if kindIs "string" $entry -}}
  {{ $provider = $entry -}}
{{ else -}}
  {{ $provider = $entry.provider -}}
  {{ $notes = $entry.notes -}}
{{ end -}}
{{ if hasPrefix "cli://" $provider -}}
- `{{ $cap }}` → `{{ trimPrefix "cli://" $provider }}` CLI — call the binary directly via Bash; read `{{ trimPrefix "cli://" $provider }} --help` on demand{{ if $notes }}. Note: {{ $notes }}{{ end }}
{{ else -}}
- `{{ $cap }}` → `{{ $provider }}` skill
{{ end -}}
{{ end }}

## Host-Specific Files (NOT managed by chezmoi)

- `~/.config/zsh/private.zsh` — work-specific shell config (sourced at end of `.zshrc`)
